laboratory_examinations.findings: Multiple hypoattenuating lesions in the liver, largest measuring about 5 x 4 cm, likely simple cysts. The appendix is rim-enhancing and dilated measuring up to 9 mm with surrounding periappendiceal fat stranding. Focal area of mural thickening involving the right lateral bladder wall with a mass-like area measuring about 1.5 x 1.5 x 1.5 cm, concerning for a bladder mass.
